<div class="header">
<a class="title" href="/gitweb/ffmpeg.git/commit/4e2bef6a82b356772a5919c51c9be1530268bd79">avcodec/cbs_av1: keep separate reference frame state for reading and writing</a>
</div>
<div class="title_text">
<table class="object_header">
<tr><td>author</td><td><a class="list" href="/gitweb/ffmpeg.git/search/4e2bef6a82b356772a5919c51c9be1530268bd79?s=James+Almer;st=author" title="Search for commits authored by James Almer">James Almer</a> <a class="list" href="/gitweb/ffmpeg.git/search/4e2bef6a82b356772a5919c51c9be1530268bd79?s=jamrial@gmail.com;st=author" title="Search for commits authored by jamrial@gmail.com">&lt;jamrial@gmail.com&gt;</a></td><td rowspan="2"></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><span class="datetime">Mon, 18 Nov 2019 00:08:56 +0000</span> (21:08 -0300)</td></tr>
<tr><td>committer</td><td><a class="list" href="/gitweb/ffmpeg.git/search/4e2bef6a82b356772a5919c51c9be1530268bd79?s=James+Almer;st=committer" title="Search for commits committed by James Almer">James Almer</a> <a class="list" href="/gitweb/ffmpeg.git/search/4e2bef6a82b356772a5919c51c9be1530268bd79?s=jamrial@gmail.com;st=committer" title="Search for commits committed by jamrial@gmail.com">&lt;jamrial@gmail.com&gt;</a></td><td rowspan="2"></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><span class="datetime">Tue, 19 Nov 2019 00:30:05 +0000</span> (21:30 -0300)</td></tr>
</table></div>
<div class="page_body">
<div class="log">
In&nbsp;scearios&nbsp;where&nbsp;a&nbsp;Temporal&nbsp;Unit&nbsp;is&nbsp;written&nbsp;right&nbsp;after&nbsp;reading&nbsp;it&nbsp;using&nbsp;the&nbsp;same<br/>
CBS&nbsp;context&nbsp;(av1_metadata,&nbsp;av1_frame_merge,&nbsp;etc),&nbsp;the&nbsp;reference&nbsp;frame&nbsp;state&nbsp;used<br/>
by&nbsp;the&nbsp;writer&nbsp;must&nbsp;not&nbsp;be&nbsp;the&nbsp;state&nbsp;that&#39;s&nbsp;the&nbsp;result&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;reader&nbsp;having&nbsp;already<br/>
parsed&nbsp;the&nbsp;current&nbsp;frame&nbsp;in&nbsp;question.<br/>
<br/>
This&nbsp;fixes&nbsp;writing&nbsp;Switch&nbsp;frames,&nbsp;and&nbsp;frames&nbsp;using&nbsp;short&nbsp;ref&nbsp;signaling.<br/>
<br/>
<span class="signoff">Signed-off-by: James Almer &lt;jamrial@gmail.com&gt;</span><br/>
</div>
